Package edu.wpi.first.epilogue.logging

Interface DataLogger

All Known Implementing Classes:
FileLogger, LazyLogger, MultiLogger, NTDataLogger, NullLogger, SubLogger
public interface DataLogger
A data logger is a generic interface for logging discrete data points.

  • Method Details

    • multi

      static DataLogger multi(DataLogger... loggers)
      Creates a data logger that logs to multiple backends at once. Data reads will still only occur once; data is passed to all composed loggers at once.
      Parameters:
      loggers - the loggers to compose together
      Returns:
      the multi logger

    • lazy

      default DataLogger lazy()
      Creates a lazy version of this logger. A lazy logger will only log data to a field when its value changes, which can help keep file size and bandwidth usage in check. However, there is an additional CPU and memory overhead associated with tracking the current value of every logged entry. The most surefire way to reduce CPU and memory usage associated with logging is to log fewer things - which can be done by opting out of logging unnecessary data or increasing the minimum logged importance level in the Epilogue configuration.
      Returns:
      the lazy logger
